<div class="row">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <br/><h3 class="center orange-text">Welcome to Mimiq</h3>

    <div class="col l6 m10 offset-m1">
      <div class="container-fluid card blue z-depth-2">
        <div class="cover z-depth-1">
          <div class="col l12 m10 offset-m1">
            <div class="filter blue">
              <div class="card-content white-text">
                <p class="card-title">Welcome</p>
                <p>What scenario do you require</p>
              </div>
              <div class="card-content white-text">
                View the next few cards to see what urls are available what
                you can do to help test certain scenarios. Note that
                get and post scenario routes allow custom configurable responses,
                with content type such as XML, JSON or error with 404 and 500
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col l6 m10 offset-m1">
      <div class="container-fluid card blue z-depth-2">
        <div class="cover z-depth-1">
          <div class="col l12 m10 offset-m1">
            <div class="filter blue">
              <div class="card-content white-text">
                <p class="card-title">How can this help</p>
                <p>Helps test how users are treated under certain scenario</p>
              </div>
              <div class="card-content white-text">
                This application has several URLs for which allows you to mimic scenarios;
                all you need to do is point the configuration in your application to the url
                for the scenario you need to test. Are your users waiting 60 seconds for a
                third party action should the service be down?
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render 'layouts/cards' %>
